section.section:
The benefits that an individual may continue to receive include:
eligibility for service retirement on or after 30 years of eligibility service or age 60;
eligibility for a reduced service retirement allowance after a certain length of eligibility service;
a normal service retirement allowance of one fifty-fifth of average final compensation multiplied by the number of years of creditable service;
the retirement allowances provided for ordinary or accidental disability;
the selection of options for allowances;
the adjustment of the allowance for increases in the Consumer Price Index;
the death benefit;
the level of member contributions; and
the length of eligibility service for members to vest benefits in the system.
